This problem is all about remove k duplicates from the start of the array and returning this k value.

Algorithm:

1. Set K as slow pointer and initialize to 1 as 0th element in the array is already unique.
2. And start iterating from 1 where loop goes from i = 1 to length - 1
     if current element is not equal to previous element we add the element at index k and increment the index k.
3. Now First k elements of the are in unique and sorted order so we return the k


class Solution {
    public int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {



        int k =1;

        for(int i =1; i < nums.length; i++)
        {
            if(nums[i] != nums[i - 1])
            {
                nums[k] = nums[i];
                k++;
            }
        }

        return k;
        
    }
}
